new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md
@@ -0,0 +1,73 @@
+# Implementation Summary: Group Commands by Categories
+
+## Overview
+This implementation addresses the issue of grouping 39+ control commands by categories in the control preferences screen to make them easier to find and navigate.
+
+## Changes Made
+
+### 1. Added ViewerCommandCategory Enum
+**File:** `AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/anki/cardviewer/ViewerCommand.kt`
+
+Created a new enum `ViewerCommandCategory` with six categories:
+- **ANSWER_BUTTONS**: Show answer, answer button 1-4 (5 commands)
+- **FLAGS**: Red, orange, green, blue, pink, turquoise, purple flags + remove flag (8 commands)
+- **CURRENT_CARD_OR_NOTE**: Edit, mark, bury card/note, suspend card/note, delete, tag, card info, add note, reschedule note (11 commands)
+- **WHITEBOARD**: Toggle, clear whiteboard, change pen color (3 commands)
+- **NAVIGATION**: Undo, exit, page up/down, abort and sync (5 commands)
+- **MISC**: Play media, record/replay voice, show hint/all hints (5 commands)
+
+### 2. Updated ViewerCommand Enum
+**File:** `AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/anki/cardviewer/ViewerCommand.kt`
+
+Added a `category` property to each `ViewerCommand` entry, assigning it to one of the six categories.
+
+### 3. Added Category String Resources
+**File:** `AnkiDroid/src/main/res/values/10-preferences.xml`
+
+Added string resources for category titles:
+- `controls_category_answer_buttons`: "Answer buttons"
+- `controls_category_flags`: "Flags"
+- `controls_category_current_card_or_note`: "Current card / note"
+- `controls_category_whiteboard`: "Whiteboard"
+- `controls_category_navigation`: "Navigation"
+- `controls_category_misc`: "Miscellaneous"
+
+### 4. Updated ControlsSettingsFragment
+**File:** `AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/anki/preferences/ControlsSettingsFragment.kt`
+
+Changed the implementation from adding all commands to a single category to:
+1. Removing the placeholder category from XML
+2. Creating separate `PreferenceCategory` objects for each command category
+3. Grouping commands by their category and adding them to the appropriate category
+
+### 5. Updated Preferences.kt
+**File:** `AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/anki/preferences/Preferences.kt`
+
+Updated the search index configuration to include the category breadcrumb for each command, making commands searchable by their category.
+
+### 6. Added Tests
+**File:** `AnkiDroid/src/test/java/com/ichi2/anki/cardviewer/ViewerCommandTest.kt`
+
+Added two new tests:
+1. `all_commands_have_category`: Verifies that every command has been assigned a category
+2. `category_counts_match_expected`: Verifies that each category has the expected number of commands and total is 37
